				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 05 Apr 2019 04:56:54 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Fajrero</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1354493</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>It's decent, but you've failed to capture the atmosphere of the Carnival of Flesh. I'll dwell on it. You see, Meat Circus is<br /> not about body horror. It is about the horror of dehumanisation. Those twisted corrupted creatures resemble people in some way, but they are not humans anymore, and that is the most terrifying thing. Not the gallbladders instead of brain or lungs.</p> <p>The first interview log deserves all the praise.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
